import os
import pickle
from django.apps import AppConfig
from django.conf import settings

class PredictorConfig(AppConfig):
    default_auto_field = 'django.db.models.BigAutoField'
    name = 'predictor'
    model = None

    def ready(self):
        # The ready() method is called exactly once when the app is loaded.
        # This is the ideal place to load the machine learning model.
        # It prevents the model from being reloaded on every single request.
        
        # Construct the path to the model file
        model_path = os.path.join(settings.BASE_DIR, 'predictor', 'model.pkl')
        
        try:
            # Open and load the model file in binary read mode
            with open(model_path, 'rb') as model_file:
                self.model = pickle.load(model_file)
            print("Successfully loaded the machine learning model.")
        except FileNotFoundError:
            print(f"Error: The model file was not found at {model_path}")
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"Error loading the machine learning model: {e}")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import pickle
import os
from django.shortcuts import render
from django.conf import settings

def predict_gpa(request):
    prediction = None
    error_message = None

    if request.method == 'POST':
        try:
            # 1. Load the model directly within the function
            model_path = os.path.join(settings.BASE_DIR, 'predictor', 'model.pkl')
            with open(model_path, 'rb') as model_file:
                model = pickle.load(model_file)

            # 2. Get and validate all form data
            age = float(request.POST.get('age'))
            gender = int(request.POST.get('gender'))
            parentaleducation = int(request.POST.get('parentaleducation'))
            study_time = float(request.POST.get('study_time'))
            absences = int(request.POST.get('absences'))
            tutoring = int(request.POST.get('tutoring'))
            parental_support = int(request.POST.get('parental_support'))
            extracurricular = int(request.POST.get('extracurricular'))
            sports = int(request.POST.get('sports'))
            music = int(request.POST.get('music'))
            volunteering = int(request.POST.get('volunteering'))

            # 3. Perform server-side validation on specific fields
            if not (0 <= parentaleducation <= 4):
                error_message = "Parental Education must be between 0 and 4."
            elif not (0 <= parental_support <= 4):
                error_message = "Parental Support must be between 0 and 4."
            elif not (gender in [0, 1]):
                error_message = "Gender must be 0 or 1."
            # You can add more validation here if needed, e.g., for age, absences, etc.

            if not error_message:
                # 4. If validation passes, prepare data and make a prediction
                data = np.array([[
                    age, gender, parentaleducation, study_time, absences, tutoring,
                    parental_support, extracurricular, sports, music, volunteering
                ]])
                
                column_names = [
                    'Age', 'Gender', 'ParentalEducation', 'StudyTimeWeekly', 'Absences',
                    'Tutoring', 'ParentalSupport', 'Extracurricular', 'Sports',
                    'Music', 'Volunteering'
                ]
                df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=column_names)

                predicted_gpa = model.predict(df)[0]
                prediction = f'{predicted_gpa:.2f}'

        except FileNotFoundError:
            error_message = "The machine learning model could not be loaded. Please ensure 'model.pkl' is in the 'predictor' directory."
        except Exception as e:
            error_message = f"An error occurred: {e}"

    # 5. Render the template with the result or error message
    return render(request, 'predictor/index.html', {'prediction': prediction, 'error_message': error_message})

                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label class="form-label">Sports:</label>
                                <div class="d-flex gap-3">
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="sports" id="sportsNo" value="0" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">No</div>
                                    </label>
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="sports" id="sportsYes" value="1" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">Yes</div>
                                    </label>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label class="form-label">Music:</label>
                                <div class="d-flex gap-3">
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="music" id="musicNo" value="0" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">No</div>
                                    </label>
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="music" id="musicYes" value="1" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">Yes</div>
                                    </label>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label class="form-label">Volunteering:</label>
                                <div class="d-flex gap-3">
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="volunteering" id="volunteeringNo" value="0" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">No</div>
                                    </label>
                                    <label class="form-check w-50">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="volunteering" id="volunteeringYes" value="1" required>
                                        <div class="radio-card">Yes</div>
                                    </label>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="col-12 d-grid mt-5">
                                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Predict GPA</button>
                            </div>
                        </form>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bootstrap JS Bundle -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" xintegrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    <script>
        const form = document.getElementById('prediction-form');
        const errorMessageDiv = document.getElementById('error-message');
        const resultDiv = document.getElementById('prediction-result');
        const loadingSpinner = document.getElementById('loading-spinner');

        function predictGPA(data) {
            const base_gpa = 5.0;
            const study_time_weight = 0.25;
            const absences_weight = -0.15;
            const parental_education_weight = 0.5;
            const parental_support_weight = 0.3;
            const tutoring_weight = 0.8;
            const extracurricular_weight = 0.4;
            const sports_weight = 0.2;
            const music_weight = 0.15;
            const volunteering_weight = 0.1;

            let gpa = base_gpa;

            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('study_time')) * study_time_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('absences')) * absences_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('parentaleducation')) * parental_education_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('parental_support')) * parental_support_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('tutoring')) * tutoring_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('extracurricular')) * extracurricular_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('sports')) * sports_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('music')) * music_weight;
            gpa += parseFloat(data.get('volunteering')) * volunteering_weight;

            // Clamp GPA between 0.0 and 10.0
            gpa = Math.max(0.0, Math.min(10.0, gpa));
            return gpa.toFixed(2);
        }

        form.addEventListener('submit', async (event) => {
            event.preventDefault();

            // Clear previous messages
            errorMessageDiv.classList.add('d-none');
            resultDiv.classList.add('d-none');
            
            // Check for required radio button selections
            const radioGroups = ['gender', 'tutoring', 'extracurricular', 'sports', 'music', 'volunteering'];
            let isValid = true;
            let firstInvalidElement = null;

            radioGroups.forEach(groupName => {
                if (!document.querySelector(`input[name="${groupName}"]:checked`)) {
                    isValid = false;
                    if (!firstInvalidElement) {
                        firstInvalidElement = document.querySelector(`input[name="${groupName}"]`);
                    }
                }
            });

            // If a radio button group is not selected, display an error and scroll to it
            if (!isValid) {
                errorMessageDiv.textContent = 'Please select an option for all Yes/No questions.';
                errorMessageDiv.classList.remove('d-none');
                if (firstInvalidElement) {
                    firstInvalidElement.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
                }
                return;
            }

            // Perform form validation for other inputs (number fields)
            if (!form.checkValidity()) {
                form.reportValidity();
                return;
            }

            // Show loading spinner
            loadingSpinner.classList.remove('d-none');

            // Use a short delay to simulate "thinking" before displaying the result
            setTimeout(() => {
                try {
                    const formData = new FormData(form);
                    const predictedGPA = predictGPA(formData);
                    
                    // Display the result
                    resultDiv.innerHTML = `Predicted GPA: <span class="fw-bolder">${predictedGPA}</span>`;
                    resultDiv.classList.remove('d-none');

                    // Scroll to the result
                    resultDiv.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
                } catch (error) {
                    console.error('Prediction error:', error);
                    errorMessageDiv.textContent = 'An error occurred during prediction. Please check your inputs.';
                    errorMessageDiv.classList.remove('d-none');
                } finally {
                    loadingSpinner.classList.add('d-none');
                }
            }, 500);
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
